    <div class="content">
        <div class="warning-box">
            <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT:</strong> All employees must follow these safety guidelines. Non-compliance may result
            in disciplinary action.
        </div>

        <h2>üè¢ General Workplace Safety</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Keep work areas clean and organized</li>
            <li>Report any hazards or unsafe conditions immediately</li>
            <li>Use personal protective equipment (PPE) when required</li>
            <li>Follow emergency evacuation procedures</li>
            <li>Know the location of fire extinguishers and emergency exits</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>üî¨ Laboratory Safety</h2>
        <p>For employees working in research and testing facilities:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Wear appropriate lab coats and safety goggles</li>
            <li>Handle chemicals according to safety data sheets</li>
            <li>Never work alone with hazardous materials</li>
            <li>Properly dispose of waste materials</li>
            <li>Report all accidents and near-misses</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>üíª Office Safety</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Maintain proper ergonomics at your workstation</li>
            <li>Take regular breaks to prevent strain injuries</li>
            <li>Keep cables and cords organized to prevent tripping</li>
            <li>Do not overload electrical outlets</li>
            <li>Report any damaged equipment or furniture</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>üöó Vehicle Testing Safety</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Complete all required training before operating test vehicles</li>
            <li>Wear seatbelts and required safety equipment</li>
            <li>Follow designated testing protocols</li>
            <li>Conduct pre-operation safety checks</li>
            <li>Never perform unauthorized tests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>üö® Emergency Procedures</h2>
        <h3>In Case of Fire:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Activate the nearest fire alarm</li>
            <li>Evacuate the building using marked exits</li>
            <li>Do not use elevators</li>
            <li>Gather at designated assembly points</li>
            <li>Do not re-enter the building until cleared by safety personnel</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Medical Emergency:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Call emergency services immediately</li>
            <li>Alert first aid personnel</li>
            <li>Do not move injured persons unless necessary</li>
            <li>Keep the area clear for emergency responders</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>‚úÖ Personal Responsibility</h2>
        <div class="best-practice">
            <strong>Remember:</strong> Safety is everyone's responsibility. If you see something unsafe, say something.
            Report concerns to your supervisor or the safety office immediately.
        </div>

